────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Pattern catalog inspirations (concepts, not code)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Hermes implements patterns researched from these projects (no code copied;
patterns adapted and credited):

- Archon V3            — YAML workflow runner pattern
- Bernstein            — Deterministic scheduling + SoD
- EXARCHON             — Cognitive recovery (3-patch + diagnose + fix-bugs)
- Composio             — CI auto-fix loop (red-merge detection)
- Hermes-Agent         — Skill memory (producer log + LLM reflection)
- Vibe Kanban          — Board orchestration concepts

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Framework documentation indexed by the RAG plugin
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The plugin at plugins/rag/ ingests documentation from ~158 third-party
frameworks per refs/doc-sources.json. Operators who run `auto:rag-fetch`
download those docs to their local ~/.hermes/rag-docs/ directory.

Each framework's docs are subject to its own license, recorded in
.hermes/rag-docs/<framework>/meta.json. Operators redistributing the
indexed chunks are responsible for compliance with each source license.
Common licenses encountered: MIT, BSD-3, Apache-2.0, CC-BY-4.0, MPL-2.0.
A few sources are vendor-EULA-restricted (Apple SwiftUI, Unity, Unreal)
and should be treated as personal-use-only.
